# Medusa v2 Conventions

This repo uses **Medusa v2** (the modular framework: `@medusajs/medusa` +
`@medusajs/framework`). Do NOT use Medusa v1 patterns. When unsure about the SDK
surface, check the official Medusa v2 docs rather than guessing — the API evolves.

> **Framework coding rules live in the official `medusa.mdc`** (vendored from
> medusajs/examples): workflow/step rules, data-model rules, service rules,
> `MedusaError`, admin JS SDK. Follow those for *how* to write Medusa code. This
> file covers *project-specific* conventions and integration boundaries. After
> scaffolding, also install the official agent skills
> (`npx skills add medusajs/medusa-agent-skills`, plugin `medusa-dev`) — see
> README "AI tooling".

## Customization building blocks (use the right tool)

- **Module** — custom data models + service for a domain concern (e.g. the
  future `minutes` module). Modules are isolated and integrated without side
  effects.
- **Workflow** — multi-step business logic with built-in retries, rollback
  (compensation), and long-running/pause support. Use workflows for anything
  that spans modules or external systems (e.g. the fulfillment pipeline).
- **Subscriber** — react to events (e.g. `order.placed`). Keep subscribers thin;
  delegate real work to a workflow.
- **Scheduled job** — run logic on an interval.
- **API route** — expose custom endpoints under `src/api`.

Prefer Medusa's existing **core workflows** (`@medusajs/medusa/core-flows`) over
calling module services directly. Use the module service directly only for
complex, non-standard customizations.

## Project conventions

- TypeScript, strict. No `any` — narrow `unknown`.
- Configuration lives in `medusa-config.ts`; register modules/providers there.
- Provider credentials and secrets come from env vars — never hardcode keys.
  Keep `.env.template` in sync when adding a new variable.
- Run with `MEDUSA_WORKER_MODE` set (shared for a single instance).
- Database changes go through Medusa migrations; never hand-edit applied
  migrations.

## Providers (match the integration contract)

- **Payment: Stripe** — payments only, **two providers / two accounts** (Mundo
  Espiritual for products, Gedelimbo for minutes). See `docs/integration-contract.md`.
- **Fulfillment: GoShippo** — shipping rates + labels. Digital products use a
  no-shipping profile / digital fulfillment provider.
- **Notification: Resend** — order emails (confirmation, shipped/tracking) are
  sent from HERE.

## Catalog rules

- ~250 products with variants; physical and digital.
- Digital products: no shipping profile so checkout skips shipping.
- The product **`handle`** is the storefront URL slug and the cross-system key
  for Sanity editorial linking — treat it as durable; avoid changing handles
  after launch.

## Integration guardrails (read `docs/integration-contract.md`)

- **Email is the join key** between a Medusa customer and a platform/Supabase
  user. Support customer find-or-create by email; do not require a Supabase id.
- On **`order.placed`**, notify the platform (authenticated POST with the shared
  secret) using the agreed additive payload. Do not write to Supabase/CRM from
  here directly.
- Keep cross-repo payloads **additive**; coordinate breaking changes with the
  platform repo.
- Do NOT implement here: subscriptions/membership, identity mastering, CRM
  writes, or the deferred items listed in `project-context`.

## When scaffolding

Bootstrap a clean Medusa v2 app (latest), wire Postgres + Redis, configure the
three providers above, set up USD region + a stock location + shipping options,
and add a Dockerfile + docker-compose (local + Coolify) plus Railway notes.
Confirm the architecture against `docs/architecture.md` before importing the
real catalog.
